<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-31T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="1073" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1073">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Gleysteen, Culver: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-31T19:00:00-04:00">May 31, 1949—7
                                p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>72. Ur 162 May 28. Dept desires most specific info possible re fol points for
                        use in replying Sov note Gleysteen detention: (1) time of arrest, (2) name
                        Sov Col referred to ur 117 April 23 who knew Gleysteen.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>